race.comment: CONCHIERO (8) pushed forward from a wide draw when first-up from a break last time out and found the front, holding the lead for most of the way and sticking on well to finish second over 1400m at Caulfield. Was tested in Stakes grade last autumn and boasts a second-up win over the handy Polymnia, which looks good form this. The sky does seem the limit for TARZING (13), though, with his impressive debut win backed up by a pattern-defying victory at Geelong. PRINCESS QUE (5) went forward when resuming last start over 1200m at Murray Bridge and held on well for second, beaten a nose. Drawn to take a nice trail just off the speed and best figures measure up. LE FERRARI (1) has been mixing his form recently including last time out when he was well held over 1400m at Caulfield. Has some work to do to turn the tables on CONCHIERO but his best is good enough. BONS TO RICHES (3) scored last start at Pakenham, making it three from four, and draws the pole here.
